msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.53:0.2"
msgid "6. Abhisamayavagga"
msgstr "6. Comprehension"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn56.53:0.3"
msgid "53. Paṭhamasambhejjasutta"
msgstr "53. Where the Waters Flow Together (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.461"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.53:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yatthimā mahānadiyo saṃsandanti samenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are places where the great rivers—the Ganges, Yamuna, "
"Aciravatī, Sarabhū, and Mahī—come together and converge."

msgctxt "sn56.53:1.2"
msgid ""
"gaṅgā, yamunā, aciravatī, sarabhū, mahī, tato puriso dve vā tīṇi vā "
"udakaphusitāni uddhareyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was to draw two or three drops of water from such a place."

msgctxt "sn56.53:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn56.53:1.4"
msgid ""
"katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ—yāni dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni ubbhatāni, yaṃ "
"vā sambhejjaudakan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Which is more: the two or three drops drawn out or the water in the "
"confluence?”"

msgctxt "sn56.53:1.5"
msgid ""
"“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ, yadidaṃ—saṃbhejjaudakaṃ; appamattakāni dve vā "
"tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni ubbhatāni."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, the water in the confluence is certainly more. The two or three drops "
"drawn out are tiny."

msgctxt "sn56.53:1.6"
msgid ""
"Saṅkhampi na upenti, upanidhampi na upenti, kalabhāgampi na upenti "
"saṃbhejjaudakaṃ upanidhāya dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni ubbhatānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Compared to the water in the confluence, it can’t be reckoned or compared, "
"it’s not even a fraction.”"

msgctxt "sn56.53:1.7"
msgid "“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa … pe …"
msgstr "“In the same way, for a noble disciple …"

msgctxt "sn56.53:1.8"
msgid "yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.53:1.9"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
